               <head>Fragment on chess</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009118886" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4058-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled fragment dealing with the techniques of Asiatic chess </p>
                        <p>The work is organised into muqaddimah, followed by two bāb further split into faṣl and qism </p>
                        <p>Contains a section on Firangī or European chess </p>
                        <p>Second bāb on shaṭranj-i kabīr omitted here </p>
                        <p>With diagrams</p>
                        <p>The work contains a reference indistinctly attributing authorship to a certain <persName key="person_f7108" role="att">Dhīrdhar</persName> of the qawm of Kāthah (=Kāyath/Kāyastha), resident in the district Mohanpur, in the parganah of Itawa, in [sarkār] <placeName>Akbarābād</placeName> (Agra) 
                        </p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 207v): completed in <placeName>Shahjahanabad</placeName>, in the <placeName>Dharampūrah</placeName> muḥallah adjoining the Masjid-i Ganjūr in the Haveli of Fatḥ Khān and Dāʾī-jān Bībī, on Tuesday, 4 Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1190/15 December 1776, Kārtik 1838 Samat, regnal year 23 of <persName key="person_70169499" role="oth">Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam</persName>'s reign, by <persName key="person_f7518" role="scr">Satī (?) Rām Pandit</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Annotations at beginning </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
